tabular.title: Screen for Child Anxiety Related Disorders (SCARED)

directionsdata.title: Below is a list of sentences that describe how people feel. Read each phrase and decide if it is “Not True or Hardly Ever True” or “somewhatTrueorSometimesTrue” or “veryTrueorOftenTrue” for your child. Then,  for each statement, fill in one circle that corresponds to the response that seems to describe your childfor the last 3 months.  Please respond to all statements as well as youcan, even if some do not seem to concern your child.

notTrueorhardlyEverTrue.title: Not True or Hardly Ever True

frightened.title: 1. When my child feels frightened, it is hard for him/her to breathe

headaches.title: 2. My child gets headaches when he/she were at school.

child.title: 3. My child doesn’t like to be with people he/she doesn't know well.

scared.title: 4. My child gets scared if he/she sleeps away from home.

worries.title: 5. My child worries about other people liking him/her.

fells.title: 6. When my child gets frightened, he/she feels like passing out

mychild.title: 8. My child follows me wherever I go.

people.title: 9. People tell me that my child looks nervous

childfeels.title: 10. My child feels nervous with people he/she doesn’t know well

stomachache.title: 11. My child gets stomach aches at school.

goingCrazy.title: 12. When my child gets frightened, he/she feels like he/she is going crazy.

frightened.title: 13. My child worries about sleeping alone.

childWorries.title: 14. My child worries about being as good as other kids

myChildGetsFrightened.title: 15. When my child gets frightened, he/she feels like things are not real

aboutSomething.title: 14. My child has nightmares about something bad happening to his/her parents.

worriesAboutGoingTo.title: 17. My child worries about going to school

heartbeatsfas.title: 18. When my child gets frightened, his/her heart beats fast.

headaches.title: 20. My child has nightmares about something bad happening to him/her.

My child worries about.title: 21.My child worries about things working out for him/her.

whenMyChildGetsFrightened1.title: 22. When my child gets frightened, he/she sweats a lot

rightenedfornoReasonatAll.title: 24. My child gets really frightened for no reason at all

afraidtobealone.title: 25. My child is afraid to be alone in the house

he/shedoesntknowwell.title: 26. It is hard for my child to talk with people he/she doesn’t know well.

frightened.title: 27. When my child gets frightened, he/she feels like he/she is choking

childWorries.title: 28. People tell me that my child worries too much

childDoesntliketobeAway.title: 29. My child doesn't like to be away from his/her family.

mychildisafraidofhaving1.title: 30. My child is afraid of having anxiety (or panic) attacks.

badMightHappentohisherParents.title: 31. My child worries that something bad might happen to his/her parents.

shy with people he/she doesn’t know wel.title: 32. My child feels shy with people he/she doesn’t know well

worriesaboutwhatisgoingtohappeninthefut.title: 33. My child worries about what is going to happen in the future

frightened.title: 34. When my child gets frightened, he/she feels like throwing up..

childworriesthingso.title: 35. My child worries about how well he/she does things.

mychildisscared.title: 36. My childis scared to go to school

alreadyhappened.title: 37. My child worries about things that have already happened.

feelsDizzy.title: 38. When my child gets frightened, he/she feels dizzy.

adultsand.title: 39. My child feels nervous when he/she is with other children or adultsand he/she has to do something while they watch him/her (for example:read aloud, speak, play a game, play a sport).

dancespeople.title: 40. My child feels nervous when he/she is going to parties, dances, or any  place where there will be people that he/she doesn’t know well

scoreAboveTwentyFive.title: A total score of ≥ 25 may indicate the presence of an Anxiety Disorder. Scores higher than 30 are more specific.

scoreOfSeven.title: A score of 7 for items 1, 6, 9, 12, 15, 18, 19, 22, 24, 27, 30, 34, 38 may indicate Panic Disorder or Significant Somatic Symptoms.

scoreOfNine.title: A score of 9 for items 5, 7, 14, 21, 23, 28, 33, 35, 37 may indicate Generalized Anxiety Disorder.

scoreOfFive.title: A score of 5 for items 4, 8, 13, 16, 20, 25, 29, 31 may indicate Separation Anxiety SOC.

scoreOfEight.title: A score of 8 for items 3, 10, 26, 32, 39, 40, 41 may indicate Social Anxiety Disorder.

scoreOfThree.title: A score of 3 for items 2, 11, 17, 36 may indicate Significant School Avoidance.

refsite.title: The SCARED is available at no cost at www.wpic.pitt.edu/research under tools and assessments, or at www.pediatric bipolar.pitt.edu under instruments.
